parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Main PNDP (Power Node Distribution Panel) Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the main PNDP can cause the vehicle to shut off while traveling at highway speeds, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off while traveling at highway speeds
loss of engine and transmission functions
and quivering dash lights and gauges.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the SAM Cab Modular Electrical system can cause multiple electrical systems to fail simultaneously, including ignition, turn signals, heater, blower, and brake lights, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: while the vehicle is in motion.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure Leading to Engine Compartment Fire
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause an engine compartment fire, which can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: Flames coming out from under the hood
flames coming out of the left side hood latch access hole
and covering the left side wing window
with no warning signs or symptoms prior to the fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and intense pull of the steering wheel to the left when applying brakes on wet roadways can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The steering wheel pulls sharply and hard to the left when applying brakes on wet roadways
making it difficult to maintain control of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rubbing of the front brake springs against the outside of the hubs can cause premature wear, leading to brake failure, and potentially resulting in accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Unusual noise or vibration from the front brakes
excessive wear on the brake shoes and drums

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel high pressure pump can cause fuel system contamination, leading to engine stalling, poor performance, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Fuel system contamination can cause engine stalling, poor performance, and potentially lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
